This paper deals with the problem of super-resolution, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses deep learning techniques, which are often associated with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of spatial feature transform layers, which are commonly used in multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of blind super-resolution, which involves estimating unknown blur kernels, a problem that is often encountered in image retrieval (cs.IR).
